= TRADITION

Threats in our lands have been here since the dawn of time; we found shelter in our tradition. Our tradition made us adress theats in a way that is unique to us, and that is what defines us. 

== The Opportunist
Taking advantage of the threats around us turn the battle to our advantage.   

Mark stress: Exploit opportunity
Mark stress: Chain Attack
Restore stress by : Changing a min for a max

=== Exploit opportunity
When a dice pool is rolled you can mark stress to reroll any number of dice.

=== Chain attack (lvl 6)
You can mark stress to perform an additionnal attack using one of your actions. You can combine dice pools of the two attacks and trigger effects that require a certain dice size or number of dice.


== The Conduct
Fighting against the threats is futile, we decided to fight alongside with them. Channeling the threats energy makes us unique.

Mark stress: Convoque Affinity 
Mark Stress: Evoke Affinity: Introduct an ambient threat 
Restore stress by : Spending time in affinity

=== Convoque Affinity
When you are in presence of an affinited threat, you can mark stress to convoque it into a vessel. The Vessel is an item that turns into a temporary ally and performs predefined actions to help you. 

=== Evoke Affinity (lvl 6)
You can mark stress to introduce an ambient threat of an affined type. 

== The Wellsuited
Understanding threats help us predict them and be prepared to face their perils.

Mark Stress: Draw Knowledge
Mark Stress: Apply Knowledge
Restore stress by: Teaching something

=== Draw Knowledge

When a situations allows you to draw knowledge, you draft one of the top 3 cards of a (Tarot / Normal) deck and choose one to keep. This card can be expanded to change the outcome of a dice roll. Beware of the number 13.

=== Apply knowledge
When a situation allows you to apply knowledge, you can mark stress and expand you knowledge to automatically succeed at a task
